Classes/SBMLightningLightnessRange.html#.abstract: Value of Lightning LightnessRange functionality maximum. 0 is prohibited.

Classes/SBMLightningCTLTemperatureRange..name: min
Classes/SBMLightningCTLTemperatureRange..abstract: Value of Lightning CTLTemperatureRange functionality minimum. Values from 0x320 to 0x4E20 represent the color temperature of white light in Kelvin. The value of 0xFFFF means that the color temperature of white light is unknown. All other values are prohibited.

Classes/SBMLightningCTLTemperatureRange..name: max
Classes/SBMLightningCTLTemperatureRange..abstract: Value of Lightning CTLTemperatureRange functionality maximum. Values from 0x320 to 0x4E20 represent the color temperature of white light in Kelvin. The value of 0xFFFF means that the color temperature of white light is unknown. All other values are prohibited.

Classes/SBMLightningCTLTemperature.html#.name: deltaUv
Classes/SBMLightningCTLTemperature.html#.abstract: Value of Lightning CTLTemperature functionality deltaUV. It determines the distance from the Black Body curve.

Classes/SBMGenericTransitionTime.html#/c.name: transitionTime
Classes/SBMGenericTransitionTime.html#/c.abstract: Value of Generic TransitionTime functionality. It consists of two fields, where first 6 bits represent the number of transition steps, and the last 2 bits represent the step resolution.

Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelRange.html#/.name: min
Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelRange.html#/.abstract: Value of Generic PowerLevelRange functionality minimum. 0 is prohibited.

Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelRange.html#/.name: max
Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelRange.html#/.abstract: Value of Generic PowerLevelRange functionality maximum. 0 is prohibited.

Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelRange.html#/.name: status
Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelRange.html#/.abstract: Status for the last operation on the GenericPowerRange state.

Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelLast.html#/c.name: powerLevel
Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelLast.html#/c.abstract: Value of Generic PowerLevelLast functionality. 0 is prohibited.

Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelDefault.html.name: powerLevel
Classes/SBMGenericPowerLevelDefault.html.abstract: Value of Generic PowerLevelLast functionality. 0 means that PowerLevelLast value should be used as the default value.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.name: northSouthOffset
Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.abstract: Value of Generic LocationLocal northSouthOffset. It describes the North coordinate of the device using a local coordinate system. The value of 0x8000 means the information is not configured.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.name: eastWestOffset
Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.abstract: Value of Generic LocationLocal eastWestOffset. It describes the East coordinate of the device using a local coordinate system. The value of 0x8000 means the information is not configured.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.name: altitude
Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.abstract: Value of Generic LocationLocal altitude. It describes the altitude of the device relative to the Generic LocationGlobal Altitude. The value of 0x7FFF indicates that the Local altitude is not configured. The value of 0x7FFE indicates that the Local altitude is greater than or equal to 32766 decimeters. The value of 0x8000 - 0x7FFD indicates that the Global altitude is from -32768 decimeters through 32765 decimeters.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.name: floor
Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.abstract: Value of Generic LocationLocal floor. It describes the floor number where the element is installed. The value of 0x00 indicates that the floor is -20 or below. The value of 0x01 - 0xFB indicates that the floor is N + 20. The value of 0xFC indicates that the floor is 232 or above. The value of 0xFD indicates ground floor (0). The value of 0xFE indicates ground floor (1). The value of 0xFF indicates that the Local floor is not configured.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.name: uncertainty
Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html#/c:.abstract: Value of Generic LocationLocal uncertainty. It describes the uncertainty of the location information the element exposes.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationGlobal.html#/c.name: latitude
Classes/SBMGenericLocationGlobal.html#/c.abstract: Value of Generic LocationGlobal latitude. It represents the global WGS84 North coordinate of the element. The value of 0x80000000 indicates that the Global latitude is not configured.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationGlobal.html#/c.name: longitude
Classes/SBMGenericLocationGlobal.html#/c.abstract: Value of Generic LocationGlobal longitude. It represents the global WGS84 East coordinate of the element. The value of 0x80000000 indicates that the Global longitude is not configured.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationGlobal.html#/c.name: altitude
Classes/SBMGenericLocationGlobal.html#/c.abstract: Value of Generic LocationGlobal altitude. It represents the altitude of the device above the WGS84 datum. The value of 0x7FFF indicates that the Global altitude is not configured. The value of 0x7FFE indicates that the Global altitude is greater than or equal to 32766 meters. The value of 0x8000 - 0x7FFD indicates that the Global altitude is from -32768 meters through 32765 meters.

Classes/SBMGenericLevelMove.html#/c:objc.name: level
Classes/SBMGenericLevelMove.html#/c:objc.abstract: Level step to calculate move speed of the level state.

Classes/SBMGenericBattery.html#/c:objc(c.name: level
Classes/SBMGenericBattery.html#/c:objc(c.abstract: Value of Generic Battery level. It represents battery charge level in percents. A value of 0xFF means that charge level is unknown. Values of 0x65 to 0xFE are prohibited.

Classes/SBMGenericBattery.html#/c:objc(c.name: dischargeTime
Classes/SBMGenericBattery.html#/c:objc(c.abstract: Value of Generic Battery discharge time. It represents the remaining time of the discharging process in minutes. A value of 0xFFFFFF means that discharge time is unknown.

Classes/SBMGenericBattery.html#/c:objc(c.name: chargeTime

Classes/SBMGenericBattery.html#/c:objc(c.name: serviceabilityState
Classes/SBMGenericBattery.html#/c:objc(c.abstract: Value of Generic Battery serviceability state. It indicates the serviceability of a battery.

Classes/SBMNode.html.name: SBMNode
Classes/SBMNode.html.abstract: A SBMNode is the object that contains all the information about a Bluetooth Mesh device in a Network. It is created right after provision a device. After add node to group (Configure available models from DCD), it will be possible to get all configured Elements and Models from the configuration object. DCD can be also downloaded manually without adding to the specific group.

Classes/SBMSubnetRemovalErrorResult.html.name: SBMSubnetRemovalErrorResult

Classes/SBMSubnet.html.name: SBMSubnet

Classes/SBMExportKeysJob.html.name: SBMExportKeysJob

Classes/SBMFunctionalityBinder.html.name: SBMFunctionalityBinder

Classes/SBMGenericProperty.html.name: SBMGenericProperty

Classes/SBMGenericPropertyList.html.name: SBMGenericPropertyList
Classes/SBMGenericPropertyList.html.abstract: Base class for Generic PropertyList functionality objects.

Classes/SBMControlRequestParameters.html.name: SBMControlRequestParameters
Classes/SBMControlRequestParameters.html.abstract: Object used to specify parameters used when sending control request.

Classes/SBMGenericBattery.html.name: SBMGenericBattery
Classes/SBMGenericBattery.html.abstract: Generic Battery functionality object. It represents the state of a battery: charge level, remaining time to complete discharging, remaining time to complete charging, and flags.

Classes/SBMGenericLevel.html.name: SBMGenericLevel
Classes/SBMGenericLevel.html.abstract: Generic Level functionality object. It represents the state of an element. The meaning of the state is determined by the model.

Classes/SBMGenericLevelDelta.html.name: SBMGenericLevelDelta
Classes/SBMGenericLevelDelta.html.abstract: Generic LevelDelta functionality object. It represents the change of an element’s level state.

Classes/SBMGenericLevelMove.html.name: SBMGenericLevelMove
Classes/SBMGenericLevelMove.html.abstract: Generic LevelMove functionality object. It represents the step to calculate move speed of the element’s level state.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationGlobal.html.name: SBMGenericLocationGlobal
Classes/SBMGenericLocationGlobal.html.abstract: Generic LocationGlobal functionality object. It represents location information of an elements: latitude, longitude, altitude.

Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html.name: SBMGenericLocationLocal
Classes/SBMGenericLocationLocal.html.abstract: Generic LocationLocal functionality object. It represents location information of an elements: local north, local east, local altitude, floor number, uncertainty.

Classes/SBMGenericOnOff.html.name: SBMGenericOnOff
Classes/SBMGenericOnOff.html.abstract: Generic OnOff functionality object. It represents the state of an element. The meaning of the state is determined by the model.

Classes/SBMGenericOnPowerUp.html.name: SBMGenericOnPowerUp
